        "muted": true,
        "reported_by_user": false,
        "raw_body": "The beginning where you’re talking about RV and IV as impacting supply and demand of contracts on the chain. \n\nMy thought process here is if you model the vol surface of MM and/or institution positioning you can get a gauge on said dynamics from the “whales” or major market participants vs retail that doesn’t move markets much in general (obv exceptions but maybe I’m misinformed there as well). If you model said dynamics from the chain, can you gain edge in gauging “auction market” dynamics and directional or non-directional movements?",
